[src:lodash-utils/page-p04] Explicit chain sequences, which must be unwrapped with `_#value`, may be enabled using `_.chain`.
[src:lodash-utils/page-p04] The execution of chained methods is lazy, that is, it's deferred until `_#value` is implicitly or explicitly called.
[src:lodash-utils/page-p04] Lazy evaluation allows several methods to support shortcut fusion.
[src:lodash-utils/page-p04] Shortcut fusion is an optimization to merge iteratee calls; this avoids the creation of intermediate arrays and can greatly reduce the number of iteratee executions.
[src:lodash-utils/page-p04] Sections of a chain sequence qualify for shortcut fusion if the section is applied to an array and iteratees accept only one argument.
[src:lodash-utils/page-p04] The heuristic for whether a section qualifies for shortcut fusion is subject to change.
[src:lodash-utils/page-p04] Chaining is supported in custom builds as long as the `_#value` method is directly or indirectly included in the build.
